<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1311" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1311">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/143.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Reported to me last night by member of mining committee that mine
                            operators of Chihuahua had been called upon by Villa for loan of
                            $300,000 gold, which has been refused. They fear this refusal may cause
                            authorities to put mining decree in force notwithstanding Escudero’s
                            circular, which has not been published as promised. I have telegraphed
                            Escudero requesting him to publish it in today’s issue of the official
                            paper.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>